        <name xml:lang="en">Formaldehyde</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">The remaining amount of unreacted glyoxal (5 % of the input) (4.8 % of the input) and of unreated ammonium and formaldehyde (4.8 % of the input) was assumed to leave the production process with the waste water. Further it was assumed that this wastewater is treated in a internal wastewater plant. The removal efficiency for glyoxal was assumed with 100% and for formaldehyde with 90%. The carbon contained in the removed glyoxal and formaldehyde was accounted as CO2 emissions to air.</comment>
